command.narcissus_farewell.tp_home_detai:
Teleport to a pre-set personal waypoint. Each dimension can have a default waypoint.
If no waypoint name is specified:
- If there is only one personal waypoint, it will be used.
- If multiple personal waypoint exist but only one default, the default will be used.
- If multiple default personal waypoints exist, the one in the current dimension will be used.
Parameters:
 1. [<personal waypoint name>] [<safe teleport>] [<dimension>]
2. [<safe teleport>] [<dimension>]

text.autoconfig.narcissus_server.title: Narcissus Config
Number of teleport cards obtainable per day

§a✦ Teleport Card Rules §e[Usage Modes]§r

§7▸ §3NONE§r: Basic Consumption
§8→ §71 card + extra cost per teleport
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Block teleport

§7▸ §eLIKE_COST§r: Proportional Cost
§8→ §7Cards equal to cost + extra cost
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Block teleport

§7▸ §aREFUND_COST§r: Cost Offset
§8→ §71 card offsets 1 unit cost
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Charge remaining cost

§7▸ §6REFUND_ALL_COST§r: Full Cost Waiver
§8→ §7Cards waive all costs
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Charge full cost

§7▸ §bREFUND_COOLDOWN§r: Cooldown Waiver
§8→ §7Cards bypass cooldown
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Normal cost applies

§7▸ §dREFUND_COST_AND_COOLDOWN§r: Dual Waiver
§8→ §71 card offsets cost + cooldown
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Charge remaining cost

§7▸ §5REFUND_ALL_COST_AND_COOLDOWN§r: Ultimate Waiver
§8→ §7Cards waive all costs and cooldown
§8→ §cInsufficient cards§r: Charge full cost

§c※ Universal Rules§r
§8▸ Block teleport§r if both cards and cost insufficient
§8▸ Set cost to 0§r for strict card-only requirement

Maximum distance multiplier for cost calculation (0 = unlimited)
§7▸ §oThis limits cost calculation, not teleport distance
Distance value for cross-dimension cost (0 = unlimited)

§a✦ Cooldown Algorithm §e[Global/Individual]§r
§7▸ §eCOMMON§r: Shared Cooldown
§8→ §7All teleports use global cooldown
§7▸ §dINDIVIDUAL§r: Per-Command Timing
§8→ §7Each command manages its own cooldown
§7▸ §bMIXED§r: Hybrid System
§8→ §7Combine global and individual cooldowns

Global cooldown duration (seconds)
§7▸ Applies to §eCOMMON§r and §bMIXED§r modes
Maximum personal teleport points per player
Blocks considered unsafe for teleport landing
Place block at feet when safe location unavailable
Prioritize blocks from inventory for safety placement

§a✦ Safety Block Rules §e[Placement Logic]§r

§7▸ When safe teleport fails§r
§8→ System places blocks from this list

§7▸ If §c"Use Inventory Blocks"§r disabled§r
§8→ Uses first block in list

§7▸ If §a"Use Inventory Blocks"§r enabled§r
§8→ Prioritizes matching blocks from player inventory
Chunk radius for safe location search

§a✦ Virtual Whitelist §e[Advanced]§r

§7▸ §bCore Feature§r
   §8→ §7Bypass cheat mode for command permissions
   §8→ §cNo OP required§r for specified commands

§7▸ §3Format§r
   §8→ §e"PlayerUUID"§r: §e"Comma-separated commands"§r
   §8→ §7Use strict double quotes
   §8→ §7Command names must match registry exactly§r

§7▸ §6Example§r
{
  §e"23a23a23-od0o..."§r: [
    §b"VIRTUAL_OP"§r,
    §b"TP_BACK"§r,
    §b"TP_HOME"§r,
    §b"FEED_OTHER"§r
  ]
}

§c※ Notes§r
§8▸ Query UUID§r via /uuid or /narcissus uuid

§a✦ Help Header §e[Styling]§r
